The paper discusses the recovery of sparse solutions in compressed sensing, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). The use of quasi-norms and the improvement of previous results suggest a focus on mathematical optimization and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves the analysis of matrices and their properties, which falls under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implications of the results, which could be relevant to signal processing and image analysis (cs.SI).
